#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:5
msgid "proxying.h"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:7
msgid ""
"The Emscripten `proxying.h`_ API provides a mechanism for dispatching work "
"to be executed by a target thread and optionally blocking until that work "
"has been completed. This is particularly useful in a Web context where "
"certain JS APIs can only be called on particular threads; any thread can "
"access those APIs by proxying the API calls to the correct threads. Proxying "
"is also useful for wrapping asynchronous JS tasks with a synchronous "
"interface. The calling thread can proxy the asynchronous task to a dedicated "
"worker thread and wait until the worker thread eventually marks the task as "
"complete, possibly after returning multiple times to the JS event loop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:17
msgid ""
"On the target thread, queued work can be executed in two ways. First, the "
"user may explicitly call ``emscripten_proxy_execute_queue`` to execute any "
"tasks that have been queued for the current thread. Alternatively, queued "
"work will execute automatically if the target thread returns to the JS event "
"loop, for example via ``emscripten_exit_with_live_runtime``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:23
msgid ""
"See `test_pthread_proxying.c`_ and `test_pthread_proxying_cpp.cpp`_ for "
"examples of how to use the proxying API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:27
msgid "API Reference"
msgstr "API 參考"

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:30
msgid "Types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:34
msgid ""
"An opaque handle to a set of thread-local work queues (one per thread) to "
"which work can be asynchronously or synchronously proxied from other threads."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:37
msgid ""
"Proxied work can only be completed on live thread runtimes, so users must "
"ensure either that all proxied work is completed before a thread exits or "
"that the thread exits with a live runtime, e.g. via "
"``emscripten_exit_with_live_runtime`` to avoid dropped work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:44
msgid ""
"An opaque handle to a currently-executing proxied task, used to signal the "
"end of the task."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:48
msgid "Functions"
msgstr "函數"

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:52
msgid "Allocate a new proxying queue."
msgstr "分配新的代理佇列。"

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:56
msgid ""
"Free a proxying queue. The queue should not have any remaining queued work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:60
msgid ""
"Get the queue used for proxying low-level runtime work. Work on this queue "
"may be processed at any time inside system functions, so it must be "
"nonblocking and safe to run at any time, similar to a native signal handler. "
"User code should generally not use this function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:67
msgid ""
"Execute all the tasks enqueued for the current thread on the given queue. "
"New tasks that are enqueued concurrently with this execution will be "
"executed as well. This function returns once it observes an empty queue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:73
msgid ""
"Signal the end of a task proxied with ``emscripten_proxy_sync_with_ctx``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:77
msgid ""
"Enqueue ``func`` to be called with argument ``arg`` on the given queue and "
"thread then return immediately without waiting for ``func`` to be executed. "
"Returns true if the work was successfully enqueued or false otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:83
msgid ""
"Enqueue ``func`` to be called with argument ``arg`` on the given queue and "
"thread then wait for ``func`` to be executed synchronously before returning. "
"Returns true if the ``func`` was successfully completed and false otherwise, "
"including if the target thread is canceled or exits before the work is "
"completed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:91
msgid ""
"The same as ``emscripten_proxy_sync`` except that instead of waiting for the "
"proxied function to return, it waits for the proxied task to be explicitly "
"marked finished with ``emscripten_proxy_finish``. ``func`` need not call "
"``emscripten_proxy_finish`` itself; it could instead store the context "
"pointer and call ``emscripten_proxy_finish`` at an arbitrary later time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:99
msgid ""
"Enqueue ``func`` on the given queue and thread. Once (and if) it finishes "
"executing, it will asynchronously proxy ``callback`` back to the current "
"thread on the same queue, or if the target thread dies before the work can "
"be completed, ``cancel`` will be proxied back instead. All three function "
"will receive the same argument, ``arg``. Returns true if ``func`` was "
"successfully enqueued and the target thread notified or false otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:108
msgid ""
"Enqueue ``func`` on the given queue and thread. Once (and if) it finishes "
"the task by calling ``emscripten_proxy_finish`` on the given "
"``em_proxying_ctx``, it will asynchronously proxy ``callback`` back to the "
"current thread on the same queue, or if the target thread dies before the "
"work can be completed, ``cancel`` will be proxied back instead. All three "
"function will receive the same argument, ``arg``. Returns true if ``func`` "
"was successfully enqueued and the target thread notified or false otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:117
msgid "C++ API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:119
msgid ""
"This C++ API is provided by proxying.h when compiling with C++11 or later. "
"It is defined within namespace ``emscripten``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:124
msgid "A thin C++ wrapper around an ``em_proxying_queue*``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:128
msgid "A thin C++ wrapper around an ``em_proxying_ctx*``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:132
msgid "The wrapped ``em_proxying_ctx*``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:136
msgid "Calls ``emscripten_proxy_finish`` on the wrapped ``em_proxying_ctx*``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:140
msgid ""
"Calls ``emscripten_proxy_execute_queue`` on the wrapped "
"``em_proxying_queue*``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:144
msgid ""
"Calls ``emscripten_proxy_async`` to execute ``func``, returning ``true`` if "
"the function was successfully enqueued and ``false`` otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:149
msgid ""
"Calls ``emscripten_proxy_sync`` to execute ``func``, returning ``true`` if "
"the function was successfully completed or ``false`` otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:154
msgid ""
"Calls ``emscripten_proxy_sync_with_ctx`` to execute ``func``, returning "
"``true`` if the function was successfully marked done with "
"``emscripten_proxy_finish`` or ``ProxyingCtx::finish`` and ``false`` "
"otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:161
msgid ""
"Calls ``emscripten_proxy_callback`` to execute ``func`` and schedule either "
"``callback`` or ``cancel``, returning ``true`` if the function was "
"successfully enqueued and ``false`` otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/proxying.h.rst:167
msgid ""
"Calls ``emscripten_proxy_callback_with_ctx`` to execute ``func`` and "
"schedule either ``callback`` or ``cancel``, returning ``true`` if the "
"function was successfully enqueued and ``false`` otherwise."
msgstr ""
